              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 32,
              "padding": [
                40,
                0,
                0,
                0
              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "pNQFx",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 10,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "v5hZf",
                      "fill": "$--accent",
                      "content": "01 · THE SCENARIO",
                      "fontFamily": "$--font-mono",
                      "fontSize": 11,
                      "fontWeight": "normal",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "RnaHj",
                      "fill": "$--foreground",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "It's the 1st. Your billing job wakes up and starts charging the subscriptions that are due. Two-thirds of the way through, the process is killed by a deploy, an out-of-memory, or a dropped connection. It restarts and picks the run back up. Some of those subscriptions were already charged. A customer gets debited twice for the same month.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.62,
                      "fontFamily": "$--font-sans",
                      "fontSize": 16.5,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "OKm25",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 10,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "D88iXy",
                      "fill": "$--accent",
                      "content": "02 · THE NAIVE APPROACH",
                      "fontFamily": "$--font-mono",
                      "fontSize": 11,
                      "fontWeight": "normal",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "GMZa1",
                      "fill": "$--foreground",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Loop over due subscriptions, call the charge API for each, mark it paid in your database. It works perfectly in every test, because tests don't get killed halfway through.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.62,
                      "fontFamily": "$--font-sans",
                      "fontSize": 16.5,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "o8Go9",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 10,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "lXijK",
                      "fill": "$--accent",
                      "content": "03 · WHY IT BREAKS",
                      "fontFamily": "$--font-mono",
                      "fontSize": 11,
                      "fontWeight": "normal",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Tz59F",
                      "fill": "$--foreground",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "The charge and the mark-as-paid write aren't one atomic thing, and the process isn't guaranteed to finish. On restart you can't tell already-charged from never-charged, so you re-charge. Where balances are thin, a surprise double-debit is a support ticket, a chargeback, and a customer who distrusts every future charge. One bad run can do this to thousands of subscriptions at once.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.62,
                      "fontFamily": "$--font-sans",
                      "fontSize": 16.5,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "m4r4l7",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 10,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "o5tcI",
                      "fill": "$--accent",
                      "content": "04 · HOW NOMBA ONE HANDLES IT",
                      "fontFamily": "$--font-mono",
                      "fontSize": 11,
                      "fontWeight": "normal",
                      "letterSpacing": 0.6
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "opkts",
                      "fill": "$--foreground",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Every charge carries a stable idempotency reference derived from the subscription and the billing period. The scheduler is built to be replayed: a unique constraint on (subscription, period) makes a duplicate invoice structurally impossible, and the reference tells the rail this is the same attempt, not a new one. Kill the job anywhere and restart it; it resolves to exactly one charge and one ledger entry.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.62,
                      "fontFamily": "$--font-sans",
                      "fontSize": 16.5,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "nNd6h",
                      "clip": true,
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "fill": "$--surface-1",
                      "cornerRadius": "$--r-lg",
                      "stroke": "$--border",
                      "strokeWidth": 1,
                      "strokeAlignment": "inner",
                      "layout": "vertical",
                      "children": [
                        {
